              LIST 
 What is a List?
Definition:
       A list is a collection that stores multiple values in one variable.
       Items are stored in order and can be changed.
       Enclose with square bracket []
Real life example:
       A shopping list — multiple items in one place, you can add, remove or change items!

Syntax:
    pythonlist_name = [item1, item2, item3]

    example : 
     l1=[1,2,3,4,5]
    names=["jos","yog","anitha","riya","yogi"]
       mixed=[1,"josi",3,"apple",4,3.5,True]
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Every item in a list has a position number called index. Index always starts from 0!

  List  →  ["apple", "banana", "mango", "grape"]
  Index →       0        1        2        3

       fruits = ["apple", "banana", "mango", "grape"]

       print(fruits[0])   # apple
       print(fruits[1])   # banana
       print(fruits[3])   # grape
       print(fruits[-1])  # grape  (last item)
       print(fruits[-2])  # mango  (second last)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
List Methods :
        fruits = ["apple", "banana", "mango", "grape"]
       
          Method                   What it does                                Example
          append(x)              Adds item at END                          fruits.append("orange")
          insert(i, x)           Adds at specific position                 fruits.insert(1, "kiwi")
          remove(x)              Removes specific item                     fruits.remove("apple")
          pop()                  Removes LAST item                         fruits.pop()
          pop(i)                 Removes at index i                        fruits.pop(0)
          sort()                 Sorts list                                numbers.sort()
          reverse()              Reverses list                             numbers.reverse()
          len()                  Count of items                            len(fruits)
          clear()                Removes everything                        fruits.clear()

